# model-training — Cursor Operational Rules
# NHAI Hackathon 7.0 | MobileFaceNet Fine-Tuning Pipeline

## Environment
- Python 3.10+
- PyTorch with CUDA (RTX 3060 / 6 GB VRAM — keep batch ≤ 64)
- Albumentations for all augmentation (never torchvision transforms for train set)
- All random seeds fixed to 42 unless specified

## Directory Contract
data/raw/          — original FairFace / IMFDB images (DO NOT modify)
data/processed/    — 112×112 aligned crops written by a preprocessing script
checkpoints/       — best_model.pt saved by train.py (spine weights only)
exports/           — mobilefacenet.onnx + mobilefacenet_int8.tflite

## Coding Standards
1. All dataset paths come from a single CONFIG dict at the top of each file.
2. Every function must have a one-line docstring.
3. No hardcoded magic numbers — define as named constants.
4. CUDA device selection: `device = torch.device("cuda" if torch.cuda.is_available() else "cpu")`
5. Mixed precision training with `torch.cuda.amp.GradScaler` to fit in 6 GB VRAM.
6. Model checkpoints save ONLY the feature extraction spine (no ArcFace head).
7. TFLite target: ≤ 4.5 MB after INT8 quantization.

## Key Hyperparameters (do not change without reason)
INPUT_SIZE     = (112, 112)
EMBEDDING_DIM  = 128
ARCFACE_MARGIN = 0.5       # m
ARCFACE_SCALE  = 64.0      # s
LR             = 1e-3
BATCH_SIZE     = 32        # safe for 6 GB VRAM
EPOCHS         = 30
TAR_FAR_THRESH = 1e-3      # FAR threshold for verification metric
